  "text": "Thus, the symmetry group of the lattice with periodic boundary conditions is isomorphic to the finite cyclic group of order N with a generator, the operator a † . This group can be used with the other symmetry operations of one-dimensional crystalline or polymer Hamiltonians. To recall, the periodic boundary conditions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] determine the number of the allowed wave-vector states in the Brillouin zone model and imply additional selection rules on certain frequencies. The boundary conditions can be generalised for the three-dimensional case by introducing raising operators for each dimension.",
